  "content": {
    "problemStatement": "Ceiling Elements\n\nGiven an array of sorted integers, write a program to find the ceiling of the given element\n\nThe ceiling of the element is the smallest element in the array greater than or equal to that given element\n\nFor Example:\n\nThe given array is: 12,23,28,34,43,45,67\n\nAnd the given element is:25\n\nThe ceiling of 25 is 28",
    "constraints": [
      "1<=N<=10000",
      "1 <= arr[i] <= 10^5"
    ],
    "inputFormat": "First line has the size of the array\n\nSecond lie has the elements of the array.\n\nThird line has integer to find the ceiling",
    "outputFormat": "Print the ceiling of the given element",
